SENATE RESOLUTION 130
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Harriet Thompson on
being named a 2025 Sterling Award winner by
the Jackson Area Business Professional
Women.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable person is Harriet Thompson, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Thompson was recently named a 2025 Sterling Award winner by the
Jackson Area Business and Professional Women and duly recognized as one of twenty Most
Influential Women in West Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Thompson, an attorney at law, has served her community with
distinction as the Hardeman County General Sessions Court Judge and Juvenile Court Judge,
as well as the City Judge for both Bolivar and Middleton; and
WHEREAS, Harriet Thompson is a well-respected member of her community and her
profession, and she epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are characteristic of a true
Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Ms. Thompson for her
many contributions to the good people of Tennessee, her unwavering commitment to others,
and her astute leadership in Hardeman County; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and commend Harriet
